helpAuth: *auth* command helps to authenticate you by EVE Online character. Send *{0}auth* command to the bot for additional details.
helpAuthNotify: *authnotify* command provides you with a link to auth you by EVE Online character as notifications feeder. Send *{0}authnotify* command to the bot for additional details.
helpTime: *evetime* command displays current EVE Online time
helpStat:
*stat* or *stats* command displays corp or alliance stats by time interval
Available mods: d, w, m, ld, lw, y, r. The **r** modifier displays stats rating table.
Examples: {0}stat m United Fleet | {0}stat d Goonswarm Federation | {0}stat y Perkone | {0}stat 2018 Nebula Alba| {0}stat 2018/03 Nebula Alba
helpAbout: *about* command displays information about the bot
helpChar:
*char* command displays information about in game character by name
Example: *{0}char Don Chack*
helpCorp:
*corp* command displays information about corporation by name
Example: *{0}corp Nebula Alba*
helpJita:
this command displays information about the item price in a specified trade hub

helpPc:
this command displays information about the global item price
Example: *{0}pc Robotics*

helpSys:
```
List of available admin commands:
  shutdown - shutdown server
  restart - restart server (if using Restarter) 
  cleartable NAME - clear all data in the DB table with corresponding NAME
  flush notifcache - clear all notifications cache
  flush dbcache - clear all cache from database
  esitoken [ID] - gets character ESI token by specified character ID  
```

helpClist:
Lists all contracts for specified group. Syntax:  {0}{1} {{STATUS}}{{TYPE}}{{AVAILABILITY}} GROUP_NAME. 
Statuses are: A - all, O - opened, C - closed, F - finished, R - rejected. 
Types are: C - courier, E - exchange, A - auction, 0 - ALL (omit if not specifying availability). 
Availability is: A - alliance, C - corp, P - public, 0 - all (can be omitted). 
Examples: {0}{1} AC my_group  {0}{1} FAP group 4

helpShips:
Ships command displays information about members who can pilot ship fits.
Modifiers: who - check members in current channel, who online - online members in current channel, all - all registered members, all online - all registered members who are online.
Examples: {0}{1} who , {0}{1} who online, {0}{1} all
You can also add group or ship name as the last param: {0}{1} all dreads  {0}{1} who online moros
